  "articleSummary": "**Summary:**\n\n\"Into the Breach\" is a technical analysis and defensive guide addressing the evolving landscape of supply chain attacks and developer-targeted exploits. The article argues that the traditional \"local is safe\" development model is obsolete, reframing the developer's workstation as a \"credential warehouse\" vulnerable to infostealers, prompt injection, and malicious dependencies. Written in an urgent, pragmatic, and slightly cynical tone, the text advocates for a \"defense-in-depth\" strategy over human vigilance. Key technical recommendations include isolating development environments via DevContainers, utilizing Canarytokens as digital tripwires, and implementing strict filesystem and secret scoping to contain potential breaches. This article is intended for software engineers, DevOps professionals, and security teams looking to modernize their local security posture.",
